Author: @aortaplatinum
Comment:
The one thing I really don't like about this game, just from what I've seen, is the godawful mocap cutscene "animation". It looks decently alright with the humans but Sonic Adventure 2 and Sid the Science Kid taught us all LONG ago that applying mocap to a stylized cartoony character design just looks like shit. And it's weird because the in-game animations are these gorgeous, fantastically done hand animation that REALLY fits the character designs, the running and jumping and everything when you're actually playing are amazing. But then you get to the cutscenes and it's the Mascot Suit Problem, "these characters shouldn't move like this", it's almost uncanny valley.
But otherwise... yeah this looks super fun to play! I'm glad it's got stuff that makes it accessible to those who aren't HARDCORE MOUNTAIN DEW AND DORITOS APEX LEGENDS TITANFALL FPS XBOX LIVE GAMERSCORE GAMERS, my gf really likes 2D platformers but isn't really as into games as I am, and I've been wanting to try this, so I'm sure it'll make a great Christmas gift for us both. Thanks for the review!

Author: @FeathersAnon
Comment:
16:40

The colour combinations and the actual way of their designs are interesting.

May's is much more orderly, thought out, and put together. She was made by a pro. She's a puppet and can be easily maneuvered.

Cody's is very thrown together. He's got leaves everywhere and is overall very messy. He's harder to move around.

May's colours are repeated and synced. The blue in her hair and pants match, with the yellow bowtie in her hair and shirt matching.

Cody's is very messy and mixed.
He's got brown and green and tan. they're much more diverse.

Even the way their pants are repaired. May's is very secure and is neat and tidy. Cody's is barely hanging on with three. They're both somewhat messy, but May's is less messy than Cody's, just to make more evidence to my point.

Overall hat's off to the designers.
